yman's ideas and passed them off as his own, though the lucky plagiarizer wasn't caught until near a century after his death.  By that point, computational power had grown to the point where even the busiest systems were able to institute the arrays, albeit with hundreds of staff, some stationed fifty or sixty AU away from their homes.%0a%3c %0a%3c With the great leaps in computational power that lead to the return to Soup travel, more automated arrays were built.  Over the following few centuries, the older manned array stations were replaced by automated systems.  The last manned Krugal Intrasystem Array was retired with great pomp and ceremony by [[Ivan Dabrian]].%0a%3c %0a%3c !! References%0a%3c # [[Berryman Sensor Array]]%0a%3c # [[Fasantauri System]]%0a%3c # [[Chronology/First Decline]]%0a%3c # [[Imperial Core Worlds]]%0a%3c # [[Ivan Dabrian]]%0a%3c %0a%3c !! Related Articles%0a%3c (:pagelist group=Macropedia fmt=simple {$Name}:)%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c [[!ImperiumEquipment]] [[!KvectonSharpAuthored]] [[!Surveillance Equipment]]%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a
